05/05/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Central Election Commission announced on Thursday (4 May) that general elections will be held on 1 October. 
Branko Petric, chairman of the commission, said that the vote will be held according to the current constitution and a recently adopted elections law.
In other news Thursday, Zenica Canton prosecutor Branislav Tomas announced the indictment of six former soldiers in the BiH Army. 
They are accused of participating in the torture of four members of the Croatian Defence Council from April-June 1993. 
(Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 05/05/06; PBS BiH, RTRT, Fena - 04/05/06)
